def niceTime():
    return datetime.datetime.fromtimestamp(time.time()).strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')

def StartOfFunc(funcname=""):
    print(niceTime(), '- START ', funcname)
    
def EndOfFunc(funcname=""):
    print(niceTime(), '- END ', funcname)

def tokenize(sentences, stop_word = STOP_WORDS):
    StartOfFunc()
    tokenized = sentences.tokenize("\\W+")
    if VERBAL: print(niceTime(),"tokenized")

    tokenized_lower = tokenized.tolower()
    tokenized_filtered = tokenized_lower[(tokenized_lower.nchar() >= 2) | (tokenized_lower.isna()),:]
    if VERBAL: print(niceTime(),"filtered")

    tokenized_words = tokenized_filtered[tokenized_filtered.grep("[0-9]",invert=True,output_logical=True),:]
    tokenized_words = tokenized_words[(tokenized_words.isna()) | (~ tokenized_words.isin(STOP_WORDS)),:]
    if VERBAL: print("tokenized_words:\n", tokenized_words.describe())
    
    EndOfFunc()
    return tokenized_words

def split(df):
    StartOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)
    
    [train_df, valid_df, test_df] = df.split_frame(ratios=[0.7,0.15],seed=SEED)
    train_df.frame_id = df.frame_id + "_train"
    valid_df.frame_id = df.frame_id + "_valid"
    test_df.frame_id = df.frame_id + "_test"
    
    EndOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)
    return [train_df, valid_df, test_df]

def concat_jobtitle_skills_row(vjobs_df):
    concat_row_df = vjobs_df["jobtitle"]
    concat_row_df.set_name(0,"words")
    skills = concat_skills_row(vjobs_df)
    skills.set_name(0,"words")
    concat_row_df = concat_row_df.rbind(skills)

    return concat_row_df

def concat_skills_row(vjobs_df):
    concat_row_df = vjobs_df["skill1"]
    concat_row_df.set_name(0, "skills")
    skillsi = vjobs_df["skill2"]
    skillsi.set_name(0, "skills")
    concat_row_df = concat_row_df.rbind(skillsi)
    skillsi = vjobs_df["skill3"]
    skillsi.set_name(0, "skills")
    concat_row_df = concat_row_df.rbind(skillsi)

    return concat_row_df

def concat_skills_col(vjobs_df):
    df = vjobs_df.as_data_frame()
    df['skills'] = df.apply(lambda row: str(row['skill1']) + ' ' + str(row['skill2']) + ' ' + str(row['skill3']), axis=1 )
    vjobs_df['skills'] = h2o.H2OFrame(list(df['skills']))
    vjobs_df['skills'] = vjobs_df['skills'].ascharacter()
    vjobs_df = vjobs_df.drop(['skill1', 'skill2', 'skill3'])
    if VERBAL: vjobs_df.describe()
    
    EndOfFunc()
    return vjobs_df

def find_synonyms(word, w2v_model):

def predict(job_title,w2v, gbm):
    words = tokenize(h2o.H2OFrame(job_title).ascharacter())
    job_title_vec = w2v.transform(words, aggregate_method="AVERAGE")
    print(gbm.predict(test_data=job_title_vec))

def vectorize_title(job_df):
    StartOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)

    print("Break Title into sequence of words")
    words = tokenize(job_df["Title"])
    
    print("Build word2vec model")
    w2v_model = H2OWord2vecEstimator(sent_sample_rate = 0.0, epochs = EPOCHS,vec_size = WORD_VEC_SIZE)
    w2v_model.train(training_frame=words)
    
    print("Calculate a vector for each job title")
    job_vecs = w2v_model.transform(words, aggregate_method = "AVERAGE")
    if VERBAL: print("job_vecs.describe:\n", job_vecs.describe())
    print("Prepare training&validation data (keep only job titles made of known words)")
    valid_job = ~ job_vecs["C1"].isna()
    if VERBAL: valid_job.describe()    
    print("Combine job title vec column")
    vec_df = job_df[valid_job,:].cbind(job_vecs[valid_job,:])
    vec_df.frame_id = "vjob_cbined"
    vec_df = vec_df.drop('Title')   
    
    EndOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)
    
    return vec_df

def vectorize_all(job_df):
    StartOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)
    
    vec_df = vectorize_title(job_df)
    if VERBAL: print(vec_df.describe())
    
    print(niceTime(), "Tokenize")    
    words = tokenize(vec_df["FullDescription"])
    print(niceTime(), "Train with H2OWord2vecEstimator")
    w2v_model = H2OWord2vecEstimator(sent_sample_rate = 0.0, epochs = EPOCHS, vec_size =WORD_VEC_SIZE)
    w2v_model.train(training_frame=words)
    
    print(niceTime(), "Calculate a vector for each FullDescription")
    vecs = w2v_model.transform(words, aggregate_method = "AVERAGE")
    if VERBAL: words.describe()
    print(niceTime(), "Prepare training&validation data (keep only FullDescription made of known words)")
    valid_data = ~ vecs["C1"].isna()
    if VERBAL: valid_data.describe()    
    print(niceTime(), "Combine vec column")
    vec_df2 = vec_df[valid_data,:].cbind(vecs[valid_data,:])
    vec_df2.frame_id = "vjobs_cbined2" 
    vec_df2 = vec_df2.drop('FullDescription')
    
    EndOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)
    
    return vec_df2

def train(train_df,valid_df, col_sample_rate = 1):
    StartOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)

    print("Build a GBM model")
    gbm_model = H2OGradientBoostingEstimator(nfolds=10, ignored_columns=['Id', 'SalaryRaw', 'LocationRaw'], ntrees=150, seed = SEED, learn_rate= 0.3, stopping_tolerance= 0.15, col_sample_rate = col_sample_rate )

    gbm_model.train(x = train_df.names,
                    y="SalaryNormalized",                     
                    training_frame = train_df, 
                    validation_frame = valid_df)
    
    print(gbm_model.model_performance(valid=True))
    EndOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)
    
    return gbm_model    

h2o.log_and_echo("test")

def trainDL(train_df,valid_df):

    print("Build a DL model")
    model = H2ODeepLearningEstimator(nfolds=5, ignored_columns=['jobid'], seed = SEED, stopping_tolerance= 0.15)

    model.train(x = train_df.names,
                    y="salary",                     
                    training_frame = train_df, 
                    validation_frame = valid_df)
    
    print(model.model_performance(valid=True))
    EndOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)
    
    return model

def show_score_his(model,interateType="Trees"):
    score_history=model.scoring_history()  #gbm_model.score_history() DEPRECATED. Use :meth:`scoring_history` instead. 
    # score_history.describe()
    plt.title('Scoring history')
    plt.xlabel(interateType)
    plt.ylabel('MAE')

    x=0
    if (interateType == "Trees"): x = score_history.number_of_trees
    elif (interateType == "Epochs"): x = score_history.epochs
        
    y1=score_history.training_mae
    y2=score_history.validation_mae

    plt.plot(x, y1, '-b', label='Valid')
    plt.plot(x, y2, '-r', label='Train')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    
    EndOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)

def evaluate(model, test_df):
    response_name="SalaryNormalized"
    pred_df = model.predict(test_df)
    perf = model.model_performance(test_data=test_df)
    print(perf)
    combined_df = pred_df.cbind(test_df)
    # combined_df.describe()
    diff_df = test_df[response_name] - pred_df
    diff_df = diff_df.abs()
    diff_df.set_name(0,'pred_distance')
    # diff_df.describe()
    # diff_df.hist()

    diff_percentage_df = diff_df*100/test_df[response_name]
    diff_percentage_df.set_name(0,'pred_distance_percentage')
    good_pred_count = len(diff_percentage_df[diff_percentage_df['pred_distance_percentage'] <= GOOD_DISTANCE_PERCENTAGE])
    total_count = len(diff_percentage_df)
    good_pred_percentage = np.round(good_pred_count*100/total_count)
    print("Good pred %: ", good_pred_percentage, " (", good_pred_count, "/", total_count, ")" )
    diff_percentage_df.hist()
    
    EndOfFunc(sys._getframe().f_code.co_name)
